cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with path planning for unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and proposes a multiple-objective optimization algorithm for the same. This makes cs.RO the most likely sub-category for this paper. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed algorithm, Angle-encoded Particle Swarm Optimization (θ- PSO), is an AI-based optimization technique. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper models the UAV formation as a virtual rigid body and controls it to maintain a desired geometric shape. This makes cs.SY a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision or pattern recognition. However, these techniques may be used for obstacle avoidance, which is one of the objectives of the proposed algorithm. Hence, cs.CV is a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with a group of UAVs and proposes an algorithm for their coordinated path planning. This makes cs.MA a possible sub-category.
